<br>
I emailed Mallo at GoB and asked a few key points to the raid.  If they help you as well, all the better <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Mallo, thanks for the tips and if you can think of anything else, please, let us know.<br>
<br>
Here are the questions I asked Mallo and his responses<br>
_________________________________________________<br>
How many people is considered a good raiding party?  Groups and Individuals?<br>
<br>
[Mallo] <br>
Hate can be done by as few as 24 people.  Now Beni wants to try for Maestro so he's going to need closer to 36 people, now having looked at his signups he's got the levels to easily hunt armor and some minibosses.  (Frankly I find Maestro to be easier to kill then Ashenbone Drakes, but my luck with Drakes is bad.) <br>
<br>
What types of key classes and how many of each might you recommend?<br>
<br>
[Mallo] <br>
At least one Wizard to port up.  At least one good monk.  At least three Clerics.  At least three warriors or high level SK / Paladins.  At least one good Druid or Ranger (must snare).  At least one good enchanter.   Some people would say must have a Shaman but I'm not sold on that. <br>
<br>
I know there are probably several break in methods out there...what is the best break in method for Hate do you recommend?<br>
<br>
[Mallo]<br>
The method I use mostly isn't the one he should use.  He has a CoTH mage I advise porting up the Mage and haveing the mage sneak around to the SW SS and CoTH groups over.  This can be a slow method of moving into place but is often the safest.  The key here is to have a Rogue invite the Mage and then invite people for Call over.  You'll want to get a Cleric called over and camped out ASAP.<br>
_______________________________________________<br>
<br>
Anyway, had mentioned you were leading the raid, hence the personal references.  Hope you don't mind a little support.<br>
<br>
Good luck!!<br>
